quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  31,12,"And truly, We endowed Luqman with wisdom: “Give<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>thanks to Allah.” For whoever is thankful is only thankful to his own benefit, and whoever has denied{1}, then Allah is indeed Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy.",footnotes:1:His grace.
  31,13,"And recall when Luqman said to his son, as he was admonishing him, “O my child, do not associate<i class=""s"">(anything) </i>with Allah; indeed, associating<i class=""s"">(others with Allah) </i>is surely a great injustice.”"
  31,14,"And We have enjoined upon man the care of his parents. His mother carried him with hardship upon hardship, besides weaning him in two years. So give<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>thanks to Me and to your parents; to Me is the destiny."
  31,15,"But if they<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>strive to have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>associate with Me whatever you have no knowledge of, do not obey them. Yet accompany them in the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>kindly, and follow the way of the one who has turned to Me in penitence. Then to Me is your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>return, and I will inform you of what you used to do."
  31,16,"“O my child, <span class=""h"">if it be the weight<sup foot_note=""80839"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">of a mustard-seed, and be it</span>in a rock or in the heavens or in the earth, Allah brings it forth; indeed, Allah is Subtle, All-Aware."
  31,17,"O my child, establish the prayer and command to what is fair and forbid what is deplorable, and be patient over what has befallen you; indeed, that is of the matters requiring determination."
  31,18,"And do not turn your cheek away from people<i class=""s"">(in pride) </i>, nor walk about the earth merrily; indeed, Allah does not love every self-admiring boaster."
  31,19,"And moderate your stride and lower your voice; indeed, the most deplorable of all voices is surely the donkey’s voice.”"
